<section sectnbr = "1D">
<servcat sctnbr = "01" scnbr = "04">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "4">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENAP70B1404003" svcinfotypenbr = "06" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Valve Clearance Inspection and Adjustment
</title>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1404003001">
<title>
Inspection
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove negative (–) cable at battery.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove cylinder head cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove right side engine undercover, if necessary.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Using wrench, turn crankshaft pulley (1) clockwise until cam lobes (2) become perpendicular to tappet faces (3) at valves “1” and “7” as shown in figure.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check valve clearance with feeler gauge (4) as follows.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Check valve clearance at valves “1” and “7”.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Turn camshafts by 90&#176; (by turning crankshaft with wrench).
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Make sure that cam lobes are perpendicular to shim faces at valves to be checked (in this case, “3” and “8”), if not, adjust it by turning crankshaft. Check valve clearances.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
In the same manner as b) – c), check valve clearances at valves “4” and “6”.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
In the same manner as b) – c) again, check valve clearances at valves “2” and “5”.
</ptxt>
</s2>
</s1>
<ptxt>
If valve clearance is not as specified, record valve clearance and adjust it to specification. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1404003002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
<spec-sdm>
<sdm-title>
Valve clearance specification
</sdm-title>
<sdm1>
<sdm-condition>
When cold (ECT: 15 – 25 &#176;C (59 – 77 &#176;F))
</sdm-condition>
<sdm2>
<sdm-condition>
Intake
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0.14 – 0.23 mm (0.0055 – 0.0091 in.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm2>
<sdm2>
<sdm-condition>
Exhaust
</sdm-condition>
<sdm-value>
0.30 – 0.40 mm (0.0118 – 0.0157 in.)
</sdm-value>
</sdm2>
</sdm1>
</spec-sdm>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I8C50A140005.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "92.624mm" ver = "01" gw = "164" gh = "246"/>
<callout>
<table frame = "all" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<tgroup cols = "2" colsep = "1" rowsep = "1">
<colspec colnum = "1" colname = "1" colwidth = "0.437in"/>
<colspec colnum = "2" colname = "2" colwidth = "0.482in"/>
<tbody>
<row rowsep = "0">
<entry colname = "1" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "1" border-right = "0" align = "right">
<ptxt>
“a”:
</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname = "2" border-top = "1" border-bottom = "1" border-left = "0" border-right = "1" align = "left">
<ptxt>
90&#176;
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</callout>
</figure>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IAP70B140001.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "50.727mm" ver = "01" gw = "175" gh = "127"/>
</figure>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENAP70B1404003002" page = "2">
<title>
Adjustment
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove tappet to be replaced. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406013"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Select proper size of tappet as follows to adjust valve clearance to specified valve.
</ptxt>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Using a micrometer, measure the thickness of the removed tappet (1).
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Calculate the thickness of new tappet by formula below.
</ptxt>
</s2>
<s2>
<ptxt>
Select new tappet closest to calculated value from available size of spare part.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<ptxt>
If the number in the second decimal place is odd, use (A-0.01) tappet.
</ptxt>
</attention3>
<ptxt>
Intake:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A = B + C – 0.19 mm (0.0075 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Exhaust:
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A = B + C – 0.35 mm (0.0138 in.)
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
A: Thickness “a” of new tappet
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
B: Thickness “a” of removed tappet
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
C: Measured valve clearance
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I7V20A141015.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "65.217mm" ver = "01" gw = "174" gh = "168"/>
</figure>
</s2>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install camshafts and tappets. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70B1406013"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Recheck valve clearance.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
